 *
* ## Overview
 * The **NSB Solver** is a high-performance C++ library designed for the numerical 
 * solution of the **Navier-Stokes-Brinkman Equations** in 3D.
 *
 * This project is developed as part of the HPSC for Aerospace Engineering course and focuses on 
 * providing an efficient, parallelizable solution for three-dimensional grid fluid dynamics problems.
 *
* ## Getting Started
 * To compile and run the project, you can use the provided scripts:
 * * @code{.bash}
 * # Compile the project
 * ./build.sh
 *
 * # Run a simulation (example with 4 processes)
 * mpirun -n 4 ./main
 * @endcode
 *
 * ## Project Structure
 * The library is organized into specialized modules:
 * - **Core**: Management of the MPI environment, Grid decomposition, and Fields allocation.
 * - **Simulation**: Solvers for the Viscous and Pressure steps.
 * - **Numerics**: Mathematical kernels including Derivatives, Thomas and Schur solver and Tridiagonal matrix structures.
 * - **IO**: Manages JSON Configuration parsing, logging and VTK data export for post-processing.
